# Simple Interest Calculator

## Description
This project calculates Simple Interest using the formula:

*Simple Interest (SI) = (Principal × Rate × Time) / 100*

## Variables
- *P* = Principal amount
- *R* = Rate of interest (per annum)
- *T* = Time (in years)

## Example
- Principal = 1000
- Rate = 5%
- Time = 2 years
- SI = (1000 × 5 × 2) / 100 = *100*

